One. Here goes nothing

I

I.a.

When I was a young boy, my father took me into the city to see a marching band. He said, "Son, when you grow up, would you be the saviour of the broken, the beaten, and the damned?"

I.b.

He said, "Will you defeat them: your demons, and all the non-believers, the plans that they have made? Because someday I'll leave you a phantom to lead you in the summer to join the Black Parade".

II

I am Jacob Keisling.

Two. Coda

Why are you still here? Get lost! Go!
